author: The Associated Press
title: 5 California Things to Know for Today
text:
5 California Things to Know for Today By The Associated Press   
Your daily look at late-breaking California news, upcoming events and the stories that will be talked about today: 
1. INTERSTATE 5 BLOCKED 
Highway blocked between Los Angeles and San Joaquin Valley for cleanup after thunderstorms spawn mud flows. 
2. DODGERS LOSE 
New York Mets beat the Los Angeles Dodgers 3-2 to advance to the NLCS against Cubs. 
3. ORCAS 
SeaWorld to challenge Coastal Commission ban on killer whale breeding at San Diego park as condition of expanding orca tanks. 
4. INMATE FIREFIGHTERS 
State corrections chief defends use of inmates with violent pasts to fight drought-fueled wildfires, says there have been no problems. 
5. JOBS 
State officials to release monthly unemployment figures for September.
